<subSubSection box="[199,1320,1522,1547]" pageId="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,442,1727]" box="[199,1320,1522,1547]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1522,1547]" pageId="4">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin substantive “ 
<taxonomicName box="[602,689,1523,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Philanthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granum">
<emphasis box="[602,689,1523,1546]" italics="true" pageId="4">granum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (grain) indicates the grain-shaped body of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,442,1727]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,1558,1583]" pageId="4">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[476,718,1558,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Philanthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[476,718,1558,1582]" italics="true" pageId="4">Philanthaxia granum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[729,822,1558,1583]" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[729,822,1558,1583]" pageId="4">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar and most probably also related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Philanthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanloni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4">P. hanloni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[245,307,1595,1618]" pageId="4" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[380,444,1595,1619]" country="Philippines" name="Southern Leyte" pageId="4">Leyte</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[452,520,1594,1619]" name="Iceland" pageId="4">Island</collectingCountry>
(see above). The main diagnostic characters differentiating both species are the shape of the frons and eyes, pronotal and elytral sculpture and the shape of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1295,1630,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. 1" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,195,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[209,1373,195,1907]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. 1 — Philanthaxia depressifrons sp. nov., holotype, 6.8 mm; 2 — the same, aedeagus, holotype; 3 — P. purpureifrons sp. nov., holotype, 9.5 mm; 4 — P. hanloni sp. nov., holotype, 4.2 mm; 5 — the same, aedeagus, holotype; 6 — P. granum sp. nov., holotype, 4.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192526/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
vs. 6) —see the differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[466,578,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Philanthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanloni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[466,578,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="4">P. hanloni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[586,676,1666,1691]" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,676,1666,1691]" pageId="4">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
